WEBVTT

00:00.096 --> 00:01.301
Previously on Suits...

00:01.325 --> 00:02.820
Sheila Amanda Sazs,

00:02.820 --> 00:03.988
will you marry me?

00:04.022 --> 00:06.357
Yes, I'll marry you.

00:06.391 --> 00:08.859
When we have kids,
world, watch out.

00:08.893 --> 00:09.994
Louis, I don't want kids.

00:10.028 --> 00:12.780
Sheila, I'm gonna be a father.

00:12.831 --> 00:14.031
Mike Ross is not coming back
to this firm.

00:14.065 --> 00:15.749
You heard Louis.
He already gave him the job.

00:15.784 --> 00:17.868
I want to know
why the hell you came back.

00:17.902 --> 00:19.586
What matters is
that I'm staying,

00:19.621 --> 00:21.405
because this is where I belong.

00:21.423 --> 00:23.063
This makes it look
like Forstman's payment

00:23.074 --> 00:24.758
never went
to any offshore accounts,

00:24.793 --> 00:25.926
and that you never took
a piece of it.

00:25.960 --> 00:27.428
That's forgery.

00:27.462 --> 00:30.130
Which is a less of a crime
than what you did.

00:30.181 --> 00:32.299
- I had no choice!
- Bullshit, you had no choice!

00:32.350 --> 00:34.184
You could have said "no" at any
goddamn point along the way.

00:34.219 --> 00:36.103
One thing is for sure.

00:36.137 --> 00:39.306
When all this is over, I'm
gonna fire the shit out of you.

00:39.357 --> 00:44.111
I wouldn't be back here
if it wasn't for Louis.

00:44.145 --> 00:46.363
I'll take care of it.

00:46.398 --> 00:48.565
"Dear Harvey and Jessica,

00:48.599 --> 00:50.284
"I put all of you in jeopardy
for my own personal gain.

00:50.318 --> 00:53.904
"Effective immediately,
I, Louis Litt,

00:53.938 --> 00:56.940
"am resigning
from Pearson Specter.

00:56.958 --> 00:58.959
Please take care of my home."

01:00.000 --> 01:06.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:21.399 --> 01:25.602
- One, two.
- Give me a second, gimme a sec.

01:25.636 --> 01:26.904
You're not dressed for it.

01:26.938 --> 01:28.906
Maybe we can get you
some trunks, go a few rounds.

01:28.940 --> 01:31.358
I think I've already
gone a few rounds.

01:31.409 --> 01:34.611
I need your help.

01:34.645 --> 01:36.580
Anything.
What can I do for you?

01:36.614 --> 01:39.283
Clients.
I need clients.

01:39.317 --> 01:40.868
Louis, the by-laws say that...

01:40.919 --> 01:42.286
Come on, Harvey. You think
I don't know what they say?

01:42.320 --> 01:43.587
I wrote the by-laws.

01:43.621 --> 01:45.989
Yeah, and who'd you
write 'em for, huh?

01:46.007 --> 01:49.426
Jessica, and she's not gonna
make an exception for you.

01:49.461 --> 01:50.627
Well, maybe she'll make one
for you?

01:50.661 --> 01:51.762
She's not going to.

01:51.796 --> 01:53.013
Harvey, do you think
I want to be here?

01:53.047 --> 01:55.048
I tried to get interviews
at six different firms

01:55.100 --> 01:57.267
and every one of them
said the same thing:

01:57.302 --> 01:58.719
It's a bloodbath out there.

01:58.770 --> 02:00.571
Which means if I can't
bring business with me,

02:00.605 --> 02:01.805
I might as well move to Siberia

02:01.839 --> 02:03.524
because I'm never gonna
find a job in this city.

02:03.558 --> 02:04.608
- Louis...
- Harvey.

02:04.642 --> 02:06.843
I'm not askin' for the moon.

02:06.861 --> 02:08.862
Just three companies that
I brought to the firm myself

02:08.896 --> 02:12.616
when they were nothing.

02:15.236 --> 02:16.787
Let me talk to Jessica.

02:16.821 --> 02:19.823
Thank you.

02:32.504 --> 02:34.555
Harvey, you don't look busy.

02:34.589 --> 02:36.840
Would you like to attend
the international securities

02:36.874 --> 02:38.926
law symposium?
That depends.

02:38.977 --> 02:40.677
Is it in Vegas, Miami, or Rio?

02:40.711 --> 02:43.347
- Poughkeepsie.
- Send Paul Porter.

02:43.381 --> 02:46.567
What can I do for you?

02:46.601 --> 02:47.935
I just saw Louis.

02:47.986 --> 02:51.054
No. He's not getting
any clients.

02:51.072 --> 02:52.489
He just wants three.

02:52.524 --> 02:54.224
Letting them go won't break us.

02:54.242 --> 02:56.577
No, it won't,
but it will open the floodgates

02:56.611 --> 02:57.945
for every partner

02:57.996 --> 02:59.913
that ever thought of leaving
and taking their clients.

02:59.948 --> 03:01.415
He's not every partner

03:01.449 --> 03:03.534
and he's worked his fingers
to the bone for both of us,

03:03.568 --> 03:05.252
and he's asking for a crumb.

03:05.286 --> 03:07.037
And I give him that crumb,
and next thing you know,

03:07.071 --> 03:08.922
all the cookies
in the cabinet are gone.

03:08.957 --> 03:10.073
You don't know that.

03:10.091 --> 03:12.793
I do know that instead
of talking about giving

03:12.844 --> 03:14.578
Louis' clients away,

03:14.596 --> 03:16.880
you should be working
on keeping your own.

03:16.914 --> 03:20.083
Jessica, I'll find a way
to keep Versalife,

03:20.101 --> 03:22.052
but that has nothing
to do with Louis.

03:22.086 --> 03:23.387
We owe the man something.

03:23.421 --> 03:25.806
And I'm giving him something.

03:25.857 --> 03:29.059
My phone rings and he gets
a glowing recommendation

03:29.093 --> 03:32.529
instead of me saying that he
left after committing a felony.

03:32.564 --> 03:34.364
No one's gonna call
if he can't get in the door.

03:34.399 --> 03:38.986
That's on him, not on me.

03:50.164 --> 03:52.616
Are you sure we
should be doing this?

03:52.634 --> 03:53.750
You really want those vultures

03:53.784 --> 03:55.636
in bankruptcy
picking through his stuff?

03:55.670 --> 03:58.672
It just doesn't feel okay
going through his things.

03:58.723 --> 04:00.340
Rachel, you haven't heard from
him. I haven't heard from him.

04:00.391 --> 04:02.309
If we don't pack up his stuff,
who will?

04:02.343 --> 04:03.644
I guess you guys
had the same idea I did.

04:03.678 --> 04:05.312
Yeah.

04:05.346 --> 04:07.681
- He didn't take that either?
- No.

04:07.732 --> 04:08.982
I just cleaned it.

04:09.017 --> 04:10.317
It was smudged

04:10.351 --> 04:12.486
and I didn't want to give it
back to him dirty.

04:12.520 --> 04:14.855
He must have been
in such a hurry.

04:14.906 --> 04:18.692
He was in a hurry 'cause
he was ashamed.

04:18.743 --> 04:22.746
I want to just
get this over with.

04:28.836 --> 04:31.755
- Jessica, what...
- Am I doing here?

04:31.789 --> 04:35.342
I'm here to tell you
that I know you know the truth

04:35.376 --> 04:36.677
about Louis' resignation.

04:36.711 --> 04:38.095
I don't know...

04:38.129 --> 04:41.998
Yes, you do, and I'm guessing
you didn't like it.

04:42.016 --> 04:43.016
You're right.

04:43.051 --> 04:44.434
I didn't.

04:44.469 --> 04:47.220
Because I don't think
that he deserves to be fired.

04:47.272 --> 04:50.440
That's funny, because I think
you both deserve to be fired.

04:50.475 --> 04:53.277
- What do you...
- You knew what he did,

04:53.311 --> 04:54.895
and you said nothing.

04:54.946 --> 04:57.564
So that's why you're here.

04:57.615 --> 04:58.782
To fire me.

04:58.816 --> 05:02.903
No. I'm here to give you
a second chance.

05:18.920 --> 05:20.220
Those don't look
like my case files.

05:20.254 --> 05:22.706
They're not,
but I didn't come empty-handed.

05:22.724 --> 05:24.641
I got you somethin'.
A job?

05:24.676 --> 05:27.477
General counsel
at Procter & Gamble.

05:27.512 --> 05:30.380
Procter & Gamble?
What is that, a joke?

05:30.398 --> 05:33.216
They're in Cincinnati, which is
like, American for "Siberia."

05:33.234 --> 05:34.267
It's American for

05:34.319 --> 05:36.219
"number 31 on the <i>Fortune</i> 500,"

05:36.237 --> 05:38.271
and it's a chance
to make a fresh start.

05:38.323 --> 05:39.606
Whose idea was this chance?

05:39.657 --> 05:41.274
Her majesty?

05:41.326 --> 05:42.859
Oh, yeah,
I bet she loved that.

05:42.893 --> 05:44.077
Ship me off
and never see me again.

05:44.112 --> 05:46.913
Louis, it was my idea,
and you should take it.

05:46.948 --> 05:48.832
Well, would you take it?

05:48.866 --> 05:49.899
No way on earth.

05:49.917 --> 05:50.951
You know why?

05:51.002 --> 05:53.036
Because this is Rome,

05:53.070 --> 05:55.172
you're a gladiator,
and so am I.

05:55.206 --> 05:57.124
Then be a gladiator.

05:57.175 --> 05:59.459
Take this job and fight
your way back here.

05:59.510 --> 06:01.712
I don't have
to go to Cincinnati

06:01.746 --> 06:03.680
to fight my way back here.

06:03.715 --> 06:06.717
I can goddamn fight Jessica.

06:08.353 --> 06:12.022
♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

06:12.056 --> 06:15.359
♪ get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

06:15.393 --> 06:18.528
♪ everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪

06:18.563 --> 06:22.232
♪ everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

06:22.266 --> 06:25.202
♪ living in a beehive
of your mind ♪

06:25.236 --> 06:29.206
♪ me and missus
so busy, busy making money ♪

06:29.240 --> 06:30.657
♪ all right ♪

