♪ the greenback boogie ♪

06:37.032 --> 06:41.132
== sync, corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==
<font color=#00FFFF>@elder_man</font>

06:41.133 --> 06:42.509
You here to pick up your things.

06:42.510 --> 06:44.661
I'm here to pick
the three clients that are mine.

06:44.662 --> 06:47.814
Those clients, like everyone
this firm represents,

06:47.815 --> 06:50.100
belong to me, and there's
nothing you can do about it.

06:50.134 --> 06:52.352
Oh yes there is,
'cause pursuant to the by-laws,

06:52.403 --> 06:53.636
you're required
to inform clients

06:53.654 --> 06:55.238
of any attorney's departure.

06:55.273 --> 06:58.475
If you fail to do so prior
to me giving you formal notice,

06:58.493 --> 07:00.243
they're up for grabs.

07:00.278 --> 07:01.528
Well, you wrote the by-laws.

07:01.579 --> 07:03.180
I'll take your word
that's what they say.

07:03.197 --> 07:05.582
Oh, I see. You don't think
I can take 'em from you, huh?

07:05.616 --> 07:08.418
Well, I'm the one who brought
them in and answered their call

07:08.453 --> 07:09.453
at 4:00 in the morning,

07:09.454 --> 07:11.421
when all you did
was take your cut.

07:11.456 --> 07:12.873
Is that all I did?

07:12.924 --> 07:14.624
Yes, and that's
why I'm gonna win them,

07:14.658 --> 07:16.209
because I deserve them.

07:16.260 --> 07:18.845
And that's what it always
is with you, Louis, isn't it?

07:18.880 --> 07:19.880
What you deserve.

07:19.931 --> 07:21.214
You're goddamn right it is,

07:21.265 --> 07:23.016
and you have some nerve
tellin' me no

07:23.050 --> 07:24.217
after all I've done for you.

07:24.268 --> 07:27.854
What you've done
is break the law,

07:27.889 --> 07:30.724
and I'm still willing to give
you a good recommendation.

07:30.775 --> 07:34.177
I don't need your
bullshit recommendation.

07:34.195 --> 07:36.062
I need clients, and if
you're not gonna give 'em to me,

07:36.114 --> 07:38.115
you better strap in,
because I'm gonna take 'em.

07:43.905 --> 07:45.122
Louis.

07:45.156 --> 07:46.623
You haven't returned
any of my phone calls.

07:46.657 --> 07:48.992
I don't like contact
during transitional periods.

07:49.026 --> 07:50.710
But you didn't even
say goodbye.

07:50.745 --> 07:51.945
What is there to say, Katrina?

07:51.963 --> 07:53.914
Well...

07:53.965 --> 07:55.715
When you're ready,

07:55.750 --> 07:57.200
I would love to take you out
for dinner.

07:57.218 --> 07:59.169
We can't do that.
You're on the other side now.

07:59.203 --> 08:00.921
- What are you talking about?
- I gave Jessica notice.

08:00.972 --> 08:01.972
I'm going after three clients.

08:02.006 --> 08:03.006
- Louis...
- No-no-no.

08:03.007 --> 08:04.090
We're gonna go do battle,

08:04.142 --> 08:05.225
and I do not want to put you
in the position

08:05.259 --> 08:06.226
to fraternize with the enemy.

08:06.260 --> 08:09.379
You're not the enemy, Louis.

08:09.397 --> 08:13.350
Jessica had me contact all
of your old clients in person.

08:13.384 --> 08:15.569
She what?

08:15.603 --> 08:17.571
You can't approach them.
It's over.

08:17.605 --> 08:20.357
I have to get going.

08:20.391 --> 08:22.159
Louis!

08:22.193 --> 08:23.577
I am so sorry.

08:23.611 --> 08:25.912
I didn't want to do it.
Don't be.

08:25.947 --> 08:29.332
If it had to be somebody,
I'm glad it was you.

08:29.367 --> 08:31.234
I'm in the middle of a merger.

08:31.252 --> 08:32.369
What's so important
that I had to come down

08:32.403 --> 08:33.570
to your shitty office?

08:33.587 --> 08:34.948
This used to be
your shitty office.

08:34.956 --> 08:36.905
And after that,
it belonged to six other people,

08:36.924 --> 08:38.375
five of whom are now gone.

08:38.409 --> 08:39.509
What's your point?

08:39.544 --> 08:42.095
That things can change
in the blink of an eye.

08:42.129 --> 08:44.097
- Louis.
- Yes, Louis.

08:44.131 --> 08:46.216
Took all of ten seconds
to scrape his name off the wall.

08:46.250 --> 08:49.019
How long do you think it's gonna
take Jessica to scrape off mine?

08:49.053 --> 08:50.253
What are you lookin' for,
Mike?

08:50.254 --> 08:53.023
Harvey, Jessica
sees me as a huge problem.

08:53.057 --> 08:54.608
The solution is just
to get rid of me.

08:54.642 --> 08:55.809
I don't want that to happen, so

08:55.860 --> 08:57.944
I need to solve
an even bigger problem.

08:57.979 --> 09:00.230
And you want me
to give you a bigger problem.

09:00.264 --> 09:01.448
I just got back.
I need you to give me

09:01.482 --> 09:03.316
the biggest problem you've got.
Fine.

09:03.367 --> 09:08.121
Sterling Pharmaceuticals
is merging with Pfizer.

09:08.155 --> 09:10.156
Come on, smart guy.
You want to solve the problem?

09:10.208 --> 09:11.408
You better be able
to identify it.

09:11.442 --> 09:13.376
There is no problem.
They merge.

09:13.411 --> 09:15.712
They only make up 26%
of the market.

09:15.746 --> 09:18.381
That's... that's not
over the limit for 10b-6.

09:18.416 --> 09:20.800
But?

09:20.835 --> 09:22.385
Shit.

09:22.420 --> 09:23.920
Versalife puts us
over the limit.

09:23.954 --> 09:25.088
We have to drop them.

09:25.122 --> 09:27.624
Unless we figure out a way
around 10b-6.

09:27.642 --> 09:29.926
Like I told Jessica I would.

09:29.960 --> 09:31.127
You told her that?

09:31.145 --> 09:32.762
Harvey, no one has ever
been able to do that.

09:32.796 --> 09:33.897
Listen to me.
You want to make a splash?

09:33.931 --> 09:37.901
Part the Red Sea.

09:42.073 --> 09:45.075
Oh, no.
"Oh, no," what?

09:45.109 --> 09:46.326
You have that look
on your face

09:46.360 --> 09:47.644
like you want me to have
some emotional conversation

09:47.662 --> 09:49.162
I don't feel like having.
You know what, Harvey?

09:49.196 --> 09:51.364
I just came in here to see
if you needed anything.

09:51.415 --> 09:54.868
- I don't.
- Okay, fine.

09:54.919 --> 09:57.454
Listen, I know that
this whole thing with Louis

09:57.488 --> 09:58.838
is upsetting you.

09:58.873 --> 09:59.989
No. What's upsetting me,
is you saying

10:00.007 --> 10:01.124
you're here to see
if I need anything

10:01.158 --> 10:02.509
when you really want
to talk about Louis.

10:02.543 --> 10:05.095
I'm worried about him.
He's in a really bad place.

10:05.129 --> 10:06.630
You think I don't know that?
That's why I tried to help him.

10:06.664 --> 10:08.098
I got him a job
on a silver platter

10:08.132 --> 10:09.766
and he threw it in my face.

10:09.800 --> 10:10.800
And he shouldn't
have done that.

10:10.834 --> 10:12.185
Yeah. Then why are you here?

10:12.219 --> 10:17.691
Because I still think
we can help.

10:17.725 --> 10:18.841
- Donna...
- Harvey.

10:18.859 --> 10:21.311
You did a good thing
by getting him that job.

10:21.345 --> 10:23.680
It was the right instinct,
but it was the wrong city.

10:23.698 --> 10:25.565
Yeah, I can't get him anything
in New York.

10:25.616 --> 10:26.950
I'm not talking
about New York.

10:26.984 --> 10:29.953
Then what the hell
are you talking about?

10:36.661 --> 10:39.129
Nice grouping.

10:39.163 --> 10:41.214
How'd you know I'd be here?

10:41.248 --> 10:42.849
Because you go mudding
when you're happy,

10:42.866 --> 10:44.501
and you come here when you're
looking to blow off steam.

10:44.535 --> 10:46.703
Well, I am blowing off steam,
Donna,

10:46.721 --> 10:49.639
and I'm not finished, so
unless you can handle a pistol,

10:49.674 --> 10:53.176
do me a favor please
and just leave me alone.

11:02.269 --> 11:03.553
Uh, how do you...

11:03.571 --> 11:05.739
Connecticut junior
pistol championship finalist.

11:05.773 --> 11:06.856
Three years in a row.

11:06.890 --> 11:08.158
What years?

11:08.192 --> 11:10.560
Ask me that again
and I will use this on you.

11:10.578 --> 11:11.861
Is there anything
that you can't do?

11:11.895 --> 11:13.563
No, there isn't.

11:13.581 --> 11:17.567
Including talking Harvey
into getting you another job.

11:17.585 --> 11:18.901
So where is it this time?

11:18.919 --> 11:20.787
Cincinnati? Minneapolis?

11:20.838 --> 11:22.422
Anchorage, Alaska?

11:22.456 --> 11:23.707
Boston.

11:23.741 --> 11:25.759
Sheila.

11:25.793 --> 11:27.127
Yes, Sheila.

11:27.178 --> 11:28.294
You got Harvey
to do this for me?

11:28.346 --> 11:30.747
I got him to give you his word
he will do it,

11:30.765 --> 11:32.298
but after you turned down
Cincinnati,

11:32.350 --> 11:34.434
he's not gonna make the call
unless you say you're on board.

11:34.468 --> 11:35.602
- I can't.
- What do you mean, you can't?

11:35.636 --> 11:38.087
Donna, Sheila values strength.

11:38.105 --> 11:39.773
She's gonna
see this as me coming to her

11:39.807 --> 11:41.558
at a time of weakness.

11:41.592 --> 11:43.693
Louis, you go to Boston
with the sole purpose

11:43.728 --> 11:49.115
of being with her, she's gonna
see that as a sign of love.

11:49.150 --> 11:52.452
Tell him to make the call.

11:52.486 --> 11:54.103
Okay, Kyle, I think
the question you have to ask is,

11:54.121 --> 11:57.240
"where do I see myself
in ten years,"

11:57.274 --> 12:03.163
and unfortunately, the answer
is, "not as a Harvard graduate."

12:03.214 --> 12:05.799
Idiot.

12:05.833 --> 12:08.835
Louis, what are you doing here?

12:08.886 --> 12:12.338
I'm here to take you back.

12:12.390 --> 12:14.841
I-I don't understand,
the way we lef...

12:14.892 --> 12:17.894
I don't care how we left it.

12:17.928 --> 12:21.314
Not a day has gone by that
I haven't thought of you,

12:21.348 --> 12:24.934
and I can't hold
it back anymore.

12:24.968 --> 12:27.070
Sheila, I love you,

12:27.104 --> 12:31.274
and I want us to be together.

12:31.308 --> 12:35.161
Louis, this is wonderful,
but it's... it's...

12:35.196 --> 12:37.363
It's just a lot to take in.

12:37.415 --> 12:40.149
To believe that
you're really ready to commit.

12:40.167 --> 12:41.751
Well, how's this for ready?

12:41.786 --> 12:43.670
I'm taking a job in Boston.
What?

12:43.704 --> 12:44.921
I quit Pearson Specter.

12:44.955 --> 12:47.841
Oh, my g...

12:47.875 --> 12:50.427
I can't believe it.

12:50.461 --> 12:51.511
You did all that for me?

12:51.545 --> 12:52.712
Yes.

12:52.763 --> 12:54.931
Well, I...

12:54.965 --> 12:59.219
- Well, what?
- I got a job in Boston for you.

12:59.270 --> 13:00.553
Louis, did you
make that decision

13:00.604 --> 13:02.772
before or after you
quit your old job?

13:02.807 --> 13:04.307
What difference does it make?

13:04.341 --> 13:06.175
It makes a huge difference.

13:06.193 --> 13:08.778
You don't call for six months,
and then...

13:08.813 --> 13:10.230
One day you wake up,
quit your job,

13:10.281 --> 13:12.732
and suddenly I'm supposed
to fill the hole in your life?

13:12.783 --> 13:14.183
No-no-no-no-no,
it's not like that.

13:14.201 --> 13:16.069
- Okay, then what is it?
- I mean, do you know

13:16.120 --> 13:18.705
how hard it was
for me to not call you?

13:18.739 --> 13:21.207
I was tryin' to move on.
Then why didn't you move on?

13:21.242 --> 13:23.626
Because I realized
that I don't need New York.

13:23.661 --> 13:26.913
I need you.

13:26.964 --> 13:29.299
Louis, geography was
the least of our problems.

13:29.333 --> 13:30.834
No, I know.

13:30.868 --> 13:33.169
And... and I want you to know
that I've come around on that.

13:33.203 --> 13:35.421
You don't "come around"
on children.

13:35.473 --> 13:37.874
I don't want them, and I'm not
going to change my mind.

13:37.892 --> 13:40.042
You don't have to,
because I've changed mine.

13:40.060 --> 13:41.895
Okay, and I believe
that you believe that, it's...

13:41.929 --> 13:43.263
Well, then if you b...

13:43.314 --> 13:44.931
I'm just sensing
that you don't know where I'm...

13:44.982 --> 13:46.048
Louis, when I asked
if you'd quit first,

13:46.066 --> 13:48.050
I was asking because if...

13:48.068 --> 13:49.686
If I believed that you
were really ready

13:49.720 --> 13:52.188
to give up children,
I would run

13:52.222 --> 13:55.325
into your arms
and never let go,

13:55.359 --> 13:57.527
but if you're doing this
because you're down and out...

13:57.561 --> 13:58.728
But that's just it.

13:58.746 --> 14:00.497
Do you understand that
I was going to change

14:00.531 --> 14:03.917
my entire work schedule
weeks ago for you?

14:03.951 --> 14:07.954
Before all this.
You were going to.

14:08.005 --> 14:10.290
But you didn't.
Sheila, please.

14:10.341 --> 14:11.291
You have to understand
where I'm...

14:11.342 --> 14:13.676
It was good
to see you, Louis.

14:13.711 --> 14:17.764
Please go.

14:30.916 --> 14:32.166
I see frustration.

14:32.191 --> 14:35.871
You see me getting
my ass kicked by FTC rule 10b-6.

14:35.872 --> 14:36.500
And?

14:36.501 --> 14:38.701
Harvey needs and update
and I don't have shit.

14:38.735 --> 14:39.735
And if you were Harvey
and he was Jessica,

14:39.753 --> 14:41.421
you'd say you're all over it.

14:41.455 --> 14:42.872
I can make that happen.

14:42.906 --> 14:44.090
I'm all over it.
Good.

14:44.124 --> 14:45.575
Donna, send a bottle
of Johnnie Walker Blue

14:45.593 --> 14:47.113
to Jonathan Palmer,
and get him tickets

14:47.127 --> 14:48.428
to the next Sox game,

14:48.462 --> 14:50.380
and then find out
when his wife's birthday is,

14:50.414 --> 14:52.465
his kid's birthday,
his dog's birthday.

14:52.516 --> 14:54.434
- How am I supposed to...
- I don't care how you do it.

14:54.468 --> 14:55.635
Figure it the hell out.

14:55.686 --> 14:56.636
Harvey, this is
a thank you to him.

14:56.687 --> 14:57.921
Why are you so mad at me?

14:57.955 --> 14:59.939
It's not a thank you,
it's an apology for you

14:59.974 --> 15:01.927
talking me into getting him
to give Louis a job.

15:01.928 --> 15:02.596
What did he...

15:02.597 --> 15:03.958
He didn't show up
to the interview,

15:03.964 --> 15:05.597
and what's happening
with our Versalife problem?

15:05.598 --> 15:06.965
I'm all over it.

15:07.016 --> 15:08.583
Yeah, "all over it" means
you don't have dick.

15:08.601 --> 15:11.937
Next time I see you,
have something.

15:13.589 --> 15:15.974
Jonathan Palmer's in Boston.

15:16.025 --> 15:18.860
Harvey got Louis a job there
because of Sheila, didn't he?

15:18.895 --> 15:20.612
- Yes.
- Donna, if he didn't show up

15:20.646 --> 15:22.447
for the interview, it means
it didn't work with Sheila.

15:22.481 --> 15:24.900
Shit.

15:24.934 --> 15:28.320
He's gonna be devastated.

15:28.371 --> 15:30.071
You bring him his box
of stuff yet?

15:30.105 --> 15:32.540
No, but I'm going
to right now.

15:32.575 --> 15:34.376
- Let me do it.
- Listen to me.

15:34.410 --> 15:35.877
Harvey's pissed at you
because you don't have anything

15:35.912 --> 15:36.962
and Louis needs me.

15:36.996 --> 15:38.296
Donna, I am here
because that man

15:38.331 --> 15:39.331
put my well-being
before his own.

15:39.382 --> 15:42.167
He gave up going
after Sheila for me.

15:42.218 --> 15:44.285
For all I know, that's why it
didn't work out for him up there

15:44.303 --> 15:46.221
and it's...

15:46.255 --> 15:49.891
The least I can do,
is comfort him when he's down.

15:51.894 --> 15:54.896
Go.

15:59.435 --> 16:00.735
Come in, come in.

16:00.770 --> 16:02.136
What are you doin' here?

16:02.154 --> 16:05.190
Stuff has been sitting
on your desk for days.

16:05.241 --> 16:07.308
I wanted you to have it.

16:07.326 --> 16:10.862
Okay. I'll need it
for my new office.

16:10.913 --> 16:12.030
You got a job?

16:12.081 --> 16:16.368
- Not yet, but I will.
- Oh.

16:17.703 --> 16:19.504
Order of the Coif.

16:19.538 --> 16:22.507
Yeah, look who
graduated magna cum laude.

16:22.541 --> 16:25.293
Summa, actually,
for all the good it'll do me.

16:25.327 --> 16:28.213
I know there's got to be
a story behind this key. Yeah?

16:28.264 --> 16:29.881
From one of your
first cases or...

16:29.932 --> 16:31.099
Mike, do me a favor, please.

16:31.133 --> 16:33.501
Just stop it, will you?
Stop what?

16:33.519 --> 16:34.519
Stop asking questions that
you already know the answers to

16:34.553 --> 16:35.770
just to stay here longer.

16:35.805 --> 16:36.805
- Louis, I'm not...
- You're not what?

16:36.839 --> 16:38.339
Examining me? Yes,
you are.

16:38.357 --> 16:40.442
You're just making small talk
while you look around the room

16:40.476 --> 16:42.727
to see if there are any
sharp objects in the vicinity.

16:42.778 --> 16:44.279
That is not why I came here.

16:44.313 --> 16:47.615
Well, it wasn't to deliver
a box of my shit.

16:47.650 --> 16:50.318
Look, when I was drowning,
you threw me a lifeline, okay?

16:50.352 --> 16:51.903
Okay, well,
that's nice of you to say,

16:51.954 --> 16:54.205
and I appreciate you
bringing over my things,

16:54.240 --> 16:56.241
but they're not exactly
a lifeline.

16:56.292 --> 16:57.993
I heard about Boston.

16:58.027 --> 16:59.961
What'd you hear?

16:59.996 --> 17:02.697
That Harvey got you a job
and you didn't even show up.

17:02.715 --> 17:04.549
Well, why would I
when the love of my life

17:04.583 --> 17:06.251
rips out my heart
and then stomps on it?

17:06.301 --> 17:07.551
Louis, I'm just trying
to help.

17:07.586 --> 17:10.505
Well, you can't!

17:10.539 --> 17:12.874
I don't have Sheila.

17:12.892 --> 17:16.478
I don't have a job.

17:16.512 --> 17:20.815
And right now I'd just
prefer to be alone.

17:32.695 --> 17:35.830
No.

17:35.865 --> 17:38.416
Well, I don't care
what he says.

17:38.451 --> 17:42.037
15% of bullshit
Is still bullshit.

17:42.071 --> 17:43.088
Dick.

17:43.122 --> 17:44.622
What can I do for you, Mike?

17:44.673 --> 17:46.875
I can see you're busy, sir, so
I'll just jump right to it and...

17:46.909 --> 17:48.376
Hold it right there.

17:48.410 --> 17:50.962
If this is your asking me
for Rachel's hand in marriage,

17:51.013 --> 17:54.799
you know, you're goin'
about it the wrong way.

17:54.850 --> 17:57.102
Sir, I think if I were gonna
do that, I'd have the foresight

17:57.136 --> 17:59.437
to ask your wife
how to approach you first.

17:59.472 --> 18:00.889
Good answer.

18:02.525 --> 18:04.442
I'm actually here
about Louis Litt.

18:04.477 --> 18:05.627
Yeah, I heard he resigned.

18:05.661 --> 18:07.629
He did, and he's looking
for a job.

18:07.663 --> 18:09.864
A fellow like that
should have his pick.

18:09.899 --> 18:11.983
Well, the partnership
agreement prohibits him

18:12.034 --> 18:13.485
from taking clients.

18:13.536 --> 18:15.320
- Ooh, shit.
- Yeah.

18:15.371 --> 18:17.772
Ah, Jessica doesn't
play around, does she?

18:17.790 --> 18:18.871
She took his firstborn too?

18:18.874 --> 18:21.826
Look, I know it's bad
out there, but...

18:21.877 --> 18:22.961
Bad? It's the apocalypse.

18:22.995 --> 18:24.278
And I'm not runnin'
a soup kitchen.

18:24.296 --> 18:27.048
If a partner
can't bring me clients...

18:27.083 --> 18:28.416
What's that?

18:28.450 --> 18:31.586
These are Louis' billables
for the last 15 years.

18:31.620 --> 18:34.839
Mm.

18:34.890 --> 18:37.225
This guy ever sleep?
And he doesn't just bill.

18:37.259 --> 18:39.144
He trains the associates,
he publishes.

18:39.178 --> 18:41.229
He will give his life to you.

18:41.263 --> 18:44.065
And you want me to do this
because you're with my daughter?

18:44.100 --> 18:45.817
I want you to do this
because I've never asked you

18:45.851 --> 18:47.652
for a thing, and
the first time I am,

18:47.686 --> 18:49.771
it's a favor for someone else.

18:49.805 --> 18:51.689
That's the kind of man
that your daughter is with.

18:51.740 --> 18:53.775
So it's because you're
with my daughter?

18:53.809 --> 18:55.660
You're gonna see it
how you're gonna see it,

18:55.694 --> 18:57.445
but the real question is:

18:57.479 --> 19:02.500
What are you gonna
do about Louis Litt?

19:02.535 --> 19:06.588
I'll meet with him.

19:06.622 --> 19:07.839
But there's no guarantee.

19:07.873 --> 19:11.626
Well, that's all I can ask.

19:11.660 --> 19:14.562
You tell my daughter to give
her old man a call sometime.

19:14.597 --> 19:17.298
Yes, sir.

19:20.936 --> 19:23.054
Hey.
You look happy.

19:23.105 --> 19:26.558
I am happy, because today
I did a good thing.

19:26.609 --> 19:28.526
You're going to let me paint
the bedroom robin's egg blue?

19:28.561 --> 19:30.145
I said I did a good thing.

19:30.179 --> 19:32.230
I didn't say
I did a ridiculous thing.

19:33.699 --> 19:36.401
I got Louis a job interview
in New York.

19:36.452 --> 19:38.186
- What?
- Mm-hmm.

19:38.204 --> 19:40.321
- That's amazing!
- Yeah.

19:40.355 --> 19:42.490
Oh, I love you.

19:42.524 --> 19:43.691
I'm gonna fix you a drink
to celebrate.

19:43.709 --> 19:45.577
Well, you should fix
one for yourself too,

19:45.628 --> 19:47.962
because I couldn't have
done it without you.

19:47.997 --> 19:49.714
What do you mean?

19:49.748 --> 19:51.966
I mean the interview's
with your dad.

19:52.001 --> 19:53.218
What?

19:53.252 --> 19:58.423
I went to your dad for Louis.

19:58.474 --> 20:01.759
What?

20:01.810 --> 20:03.761
It's really sweet.

20:03.812 --> 20:06.380
But...

20:06.398 --> 20:07.815
Let's just say
there's a reason

20:07.850 --> 20:10.602
that I didn't go to my dad
to pay for law school.

20:10.653 --> 20:11.603
I thought you said it was
because you wanted

20:11.654 --> 20:12.904
to do it yourself.

20:12.938 --> 20:15.857
It is, but other people
don't have a problem

20:15.891 --> 20:17.325
going to their parents

20:17.359 --> 20:21.395
because they don't have to wait
for the other shoe to drop.

20:21.413 --> 20:23.198
What are you talking about?

20:23.232 --> 20:24.766
He's not gonna
give something for nothing.

20:24.800 --> 20:26.868
So you mean after this, he's
gonna want something from me?

20:26.902 --> 20:32.073
I don't know, but he's gonna
want something from someone.

20:32.091 --> 20:36.794
If it gets Louis a fresh
start, I really don't care.

20:44.783 --> 20:46.039
Oh man....

20:46.064 --> 20:47.681
Really?
Yeah.

20:47.732 --> 20:48.815
- You got to be kiddin' me.
- No.

20:48.850 --> 20:50.100
You went there too?

20:50.134 --> 20:51.151
Every Tuesday
for the last five years.

20:51.185 --> 20:53.487
Oh. Wednesday.

20:53.521 --> 20:56.189
Chicken parm day.

20:56.240 --> 20:57.240
More like Christmas to me.

20:57.275 --> 20:58.608
- Oh, I believe it.
- Oh, Louis.

20:58.642 --> 21:00.027
This has been a pleasure,

21:00.078 --> 21:03.113
but it's time that we got
down to the crux of the matter.

21:03.147 --> 21:04.414
You want to know
why I resigned.

21:04.449 --> 21:05.982
Well, I did call Jessica,

21:06.000 --> 21:08.001
and she gave you
a glowing recommendation,

21:08.036 --> 21:09.503
and we both know
that's bullshit.

21:09.537 --> 21:11.004
You want to know the truth.

21:11.039 --> 21:12.655
Did I say anything
about the truth?

21:12.674 --> 21:15.042
I'm just makin' sure you know
I know that it's bullshit.

21:15.093 --> 21:17.461
But my truth is,
I don't care why you left.

21:17.495 --> 21:19.463
All I care about
is what you're gonna take.

21:19.497 --> 21:20.697
What?

21:20.732 --> 21:23.200
You take one client,
I could give a shit

21:23.234 --> 21:25.835
How big it is, and I'll make you
a senior partner on the spot.

21:25.853 --> 21:27.104
Wait a second.

21:27.138 --> 21:29.056
Mike Ross said

21:29.107 --> 21:31.358
that I was not required
to bring business.

21:31.392 --> 21:32.976
This isn't about business.

21:33.010 --> 21:34.728
This is about balls.

21:34.779 --> 21:35.979
I don't need another grinder,

21:36.013 --> 21:37.781
I need a lawyer
who can kick a door in,

21:37.815 --> 21:39.733
and the door in question
is Pearson Specter's.

21:39.784 --> 21:41.785
You want to see if I can break
my partnership agreement?

21:41.819 --> 21:43.286
You're damn right I do,

21:43.321 --> 21:47.124
because if you can't do that,
then what the hell good are you?

21:48.993 --> 21:50.026
You're no different
than Jessica.

21:51.162 --> 21:53.630
I'll take that
as a compliment.

21:53.664 --> 21:54.664
Well, if you'll excuse me,

21:54.698 --> 21:56.750
Sylvia will validate you
on the way out.

21:56.801 --> 21:57.918
Yeah, well,

21:57.969 --> 22:00.504
Robert, this is New York.
I take a cab.

22:00.538 --> 22:03.507
See, that's my way
of saying "get the hell out."

22:11.649 --> 22:12.983
Well, how long
is a little while?

22:13.017 --> 22:14.351
Do you have any...

22:14.385 --> 22:15.519
Louis!

22:15.553 --> 22:17.354
Excuse me.

22:17.388 --> 22:19.072
Katrina, what are
you doing here?

22:19.107 --> 22:20.690
You know what I'm doing here.
This isn't your client anymore.

22:20.724 --> 22:22.909
You're prohibited
from contacting them.

22:22.944 --> 22:25.412
- I-I'm not here to see...
- Neubacher Capital?

22:25.446 --> 22:26.997
Yes, you are.

22:27.031 --> 22:28.615
Just like you're going
to go see Carver Tech

22:28.666 --> 22:30.867
and Blackthorne Simons.

22:30.901 --> 22:32.619
How do you know that?

22:32.670 --> 22:34.287
- Because they called me.
- What are they saying?

22:34.338 --> 22:35.699
Doesn't matter
what they're saying.

22:35.706 --> 22:37.257
It's plain as day
you're trying to poach them.

22:37.291 --> 22:38.875
- Does Jessica know?
- Not yet.

22:38.909 --> 22:40.210
But if you keep doing this,
she's gonna find out.

22:40.244 --> 22:41.428
Yeah, well, let her sue me,

22:41.462 --> 22:42.745
'cause I don't have
any other choice.

22:42.764 --> 22:43.764
What are you talking about?

22:43.798 --> 22:45.265
Robert Zane offered me
senior partner

22:45.299 --> 22:46.800
if I can break
the partnership agreement.

22:46.851 --> 22:49.519
That is a major law firm
in New York.

22:49.554 --> 22:50.854
I'm not gonna get
a better chance than that.

22:50.888 --> 22:51.888
Louis...

22:51.889 --> 22:53.440
Look, tell Jessica
if you have to.

22:53.474 --> 22:55.809
I don't want to get you
in trouble, okay?

22:55.860 --> 22:59.596
But I just lost my job.

22:59.614 --> 23:01.731
And I just lost the woman
I love for the second time,

23:01.765 --> 23:03.483
all in one week.

23:03.534 --> 23:06.936
Now I have this chance
to turn my life around...

23:06.954 --> 23:11.107
with this one client.

23:11.125 --> 23:14.544
I'm gonna take it.

23:14.579 --> 23:17.664
Louis.

23:20.835 --> 23:23.720
You want one client,
I'll give you one client.

23:23.754 --> 23:25.955
What? Wait, no...

23:25.973 --> 23:27.757
When you agreed to take me on,

23:27.791 --> 23:30.143
I swore that
I would be loyal to you,

23:30.178 --> 23:32.929
and if I'm not loyal now,
then I never was.

23:32.963 --> 23:35.515
Katrina, if you do this
and Jessica figures it out,

23:35.566 --> 23:37.267
she will fire you,

23:37.301 --> 23:39.019
and I cannot live with that.

23:39.070 --> 23:40.937
That won't matter
if you get the job

23:40.971 --> 23:44.641
and you take me with you.

23:44.659 --> 23:48.778
Give me the goddamn name.

23:50.248 --> 23:51.832
What?

23:51.866 --> 23:53.116
I'm gonna tell you something,

23:53.150 --> 23:55.418
and I don't want
you to overreact.

23:55.453 --> 23:57.787
From the look on your face,
I'm not makin' any promises.

23:57.821 --> 23:58.821
I just got an email
from Louis.

23:58.840 --> 24:00.624
He's going after Versalife.

24:00.658 --> 24:02.342
- Get me Ray.
- What are you gonna do?

24:02.376 --> 24:03.960
Get me Ray!

24:03.994 --> 24:05.428
Harvey, it was just
a notification email.

24:05.463 --> 24:07.681
You don't even know where he is!
Yes, I do.

24:07.715 --> 24:08.849
What are you talking about?

24:08.883 --> 24:11.551
That notification is required
by the bylaws.

24:11.602 --> 24:13.186
He's doing it
at the last second.

24:13.221 --> 24:15.805
I guarantee you he's walking
in Versalife's door right now.

24:20.528 --> 24:23.680
Hell do you think
you're doing?

24:23.698 --> 24:25.949
Not doing, did.
I just signed Versalife.

24:25.983 --> 24:27.984
- You have no right.
- Please, I have every right.

24:28.018 --> 24:30.353
Because when I quit, Jessica
only notified my clients,

24:30.371 --> 24:31.621
not yours,
because she didn't think

24:31.656 --> 24:33.189
I had enough balls
to go after you head-on.

24:33.207 --> 24:34.541
That wasn't her, that was me,

24:34.575 --> 24:36.826
because I didn't think
you would stoop this low.

24:36.860 --> 24:39.362
Oh, too bad. You exposed
your flank, now you're too late.

24:39.380 --> 24:41.364
Yeah, and you can see
the fear in my eyes.

24:41.382 --> 24:42.999
Excuse me.

24:43.033 --> 24:45.368
I told you, you're too late.

24:45.386 --> 24:46.920
To tell them
an unemployed clown

24:46.971 --> 24:48.838
just sold them
a pile of bullshit?

24:48.872 --> 24:52.392
You mean the bullshit that you
have to drop them as a client?

24:52.426 --> 24:53.560
The Pfizer merger.

24:53.594 --> 24:55.729
FTC rule 10b-6.

24:55.763 --> 24:58.014
They were not pleased
that you kept them in the dark.

24:58.048 --> 25:00.066
- You are a son of a bitch.
- Who's the clown now?

25:00.101 --> 25:01.518
You're a son of a bitch.

25:01.552 --> 25:02.819
I'm only taking one client

25:02.853 --> 25:04.220
that you're gonna
have to drop anyway.

25:04.238 --> 25:05.388
The least you could do
is be a gentleman about it.

25:05.406 --> 25:07.490
A gentleman?
I got you two jobs!

25:07.525 --> 25:10.277
Two jobs in Siberia!

25:10.328 --> 25:12.562
Out of pity.

